What is MUI-FReq
****************

   Well... if you are a Fido Point, you'll guess what is @{b}MUI-FReq@{ub}.
However, that's it...

   @{b}MUI-FReq@{ub} is a tool to create and manipulate the @{b}.REQ@{ub} files used by
TrapDoor and other Fidonet mailers to request files from nodes. It has
a lot of features not found on others similar programs. They are:

   @{b}*@{ub} An Easy-To-Use @{b}MUI@{ub} interface. @{b}MUI@{ub} is copyrighted by Stefan Stuntz,
     and is not included in the distribution archive. You can obtain it
     from various BBS, or directly from Stefan.

   @{b}*@{ub} The capability to create and use backups for the filelists. Never
     happened you call your favourite BBS to get the latest 100 PD
     utilities, and some of them aren't available? You have to rewrite
     the 100 names, and hope the next time they are there...

   @{b}*@{ub} An Outbound scan facility that allows you to see what nodes have
     pending file requests. So you can load them and poll the node.

   @{b}*@{ub} An Inbound scan facility that allows you to delete from the
     filelist the files that you have just downloaded. This is great
     used with the backup option.

   @{b}*@{ub} Full localization of the program. Only the Italian catalog is
     available, but you can do your own translation and send it to me.
     It will be included in the next release.

   @{b}*@{ub} Direct polling from the program, using your favourite mailer. The
     address of the node can be put in the command string, making
     multi-polling very easy.

   @{b}*@{ub} A filelist browser, useful for selecting filenames directly from a
     BBS file list.  This is not yet implemented, but will be in the
     next release.

   @{b}*@{ub} An ARexx interface, to use @{b}MUI-FReq@{ub} with your favourite reader.
     Also this isn't yet implemented, but will be very soon.

   Have fun with @{b}MUI-FReq@{ub}!


@EndNode

